headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball had a season-high 32 points and the Charlotte Hornets held off a furious second-half rally from Indiana's backups to beat the Pacers 121-118 on Friday night for their fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball scores 32 points, Hornets hold off Pacers 121-118

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole and Andrew Wiggins made the most of their opportunity to step up as scorers in Stephen Curry's absence.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poole helps Curry-less Warriors beat Pistons 105-102

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum grew up idolizing Kobe Bryant, so he knew all about the Celtics-Lakers rivalry even before becoming part of it.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 37, Celtics beat Lakers in James' return

headlines.description: — The shots were not falling for James Harden on Friday, except when he was at the free throw line.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden rallies Nets to 115-113 win over Magic as Durant sits

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 21 points, 19 rebounds and seven assists to help the Milwaukee Bucks withstand Oklahoma City’s comeback attempt and beat the Thunder 96-89 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks build big lead, hang on to beat Thunder 96-89

events.name: LA Clippers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Jonas Valanciunas had 26 points and 13 rebounds and the New Orleans Pelicans overcame a 20-point first-half deficit to beat the Los Angeles Clippers 94-81 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Valanciunas, Hart, Ingram lead Pelicans past Clippers, 94-81

headlines.description: — Chris Paul has piled up plenty of points and assists during his 17 seasons in the NBA.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns rally in 4th, beat Mavs 112-104 for 11th straight win

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 18 of his season-high 32 points in the first half and the Toronto Raptors continued their recent dominance in Sacramento, thumping the Kings 108-89 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam's 32 help Raptors beat Kings 108-89 to end skid
